The paper proposes a new algorithm for Neural Architecture Search (NAS) that improves upon the current state-of-the-art. NAS is a subfield of machine learning that involves searching for the optimal neural network architecture for a given task. The paper specifically focuses on Differentiable NAS, which is a recent approach that has gained popularity due to its computational efficiency. The paper discusses the optimization challenges of Differentiable NAS and proposes a new algorithm that addresses these challenges. Given the focus on optimization and machine learning, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), and cs.AR (Hardware Architecture).
